comment_data.body:
@hugbubby I was thinking about that. Probably, I'm afraid, that communication (encrypted, of course) will be available for _everybody_, not only the chosen ones. Right now Alice can traceroute to Bob's IP address and be aware who is able to collect her messages. If she has high paranoia level - she can make a VPN tunnel, use some techniques to conceal metainformation and so on.
If we go with IPFS, she can do... nothing. She can just prey that nobody:
1. find a bug in random generator;
2. find linear correlation between Sbox constants;
3. discover effective factorization algorithm;
4. create true quantum computer;
5. ???
Then our messages may become a big data for somebody's bachelor degree diploma in 2030 :(

I just want to ask to make this IPFS feature optional if we implement it.
